<br />
<br />Here's a book written using Hamlib:
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.cc.gatech.edu/classes/AY2006/cs2260_spring/gbabook/">http://www.cc.gatech.edu/classes/AY2006 ... g/gbabook/</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Alot of what you learn about working with tile based graphics can then be applied in Nes C dev.  I personally think nes dev is a little too picky for a straight C beginner...it frustrates me and i've been hobby coding since 2004. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

